serves two (halved from Adam Liaw's recipe)

[ dashi ]
- 2 x niboshi (dried anchovies)
  - remove head and black intestines by pinching with fingers
- 1 litre water
- 1 small piece (7g) kombu (dried kelp)
- 2 dried shitake mushrooms
- a sprinkle of bonito flakes
  - alternatively 1 tsp bonito soup stock (katsuo dashi)

[ dashi seasoning ]
- 16.5g (1.5 tbsp) soy
- 12g (1 tbsp) mirin
- 5g (1 tsp) sugar
- salt to taste

- add niboshi, water, kombu and shitake to saucepan
- bring to simmer
- remove kombu when water starts to steam
- add bonito flakes (if using bonito dashi)
- turn off heat
- let stand for 20 mins
- strain
- add dashi seasoning and adjust taste
- add frozen udon cakes to simmering water until just separated
